          systems, microcontrollers, and structured technical problem-solving. That foundation
          naturally led me to explore how software can automate and improve complex real-world processes.
        </p>

        <p class="text-secondary">
          Currently I work as aWarehouse Operations Supervisor, coordinating
          high-volume warehouse operations and managing daily outbound flows. Working in this
          environment exposed me to many inefficiencies in manual processes — which pushed me
          to start building small digital tools to improve data visibility, track workflows,
          and simplify operational decisions.
        </p>

        <p class="text-secondary">
          To deepen my development skills, I completed the
          Le Wagon Full-Stack Web Development Bootcamp, where I built several
          applications usingRuby on Rails, JavaScript, PostgreSQL, and modern web tools.
          My projects focus on solving practical problems — from internal operational tools
          to platforms likeVeloFind, an application designed to help people
          recover stolen bikes.
        </p>

        <p class="text-secondary">
          I’m particularly interested in the engineering side of software — designing application logic,
          structuring data, and building systems that improve how processes run in the real world.
          While I enjoy working across the full stack, I’m especially drawn to backend development
          where architecture, reliability, and system design play a central role.
        </p>

